{
  "text": "We may assume that the diversity of this old field is not driven by one dominant grass but by many interacting forces. Though we suggest some beneficial effects from endophytes in our study (drought tolerance), an obligate mutualism has not been shown. The level to which mutualistic endophytes are beneficial to grasses in natural systems has been questioned for a number of reasons. [CITATION_1] argue that unlike the highly controlled agricultural studies conducted thus far, endophyte-plant-herbivore interactions should be more variable in natural systems. Other supporting arguments include the following:",
